launches.launchDescription: The thirteenth Starlink launch for SpaceX.

launches.launchName: Northrop Grumman Resupply Mission to Space Station (CRS 14)
launches.launchDescription: This is the fourteenth contracted commercial resupply services mission for Northrop Grumman, launching its Cygnus spacecraft aboard an Antares rocket from Wallops Flight Facility in Virginia. It will deliver several tons of cargo and supplies to the International Space Station.

NASA astronaut Kate Rubins and cosmonauts Sergey Ryzhikov and Sergey Kud Sverchkov of the Russian space agency Roscosmos launch aboard a Soyuz spacecraft to the International Space Station. This will be the second spaceflight for Rubins.

launches.launchName: OSIRIS REx Collects a Sample from Asteroid Bennu
launches.launchDescription: Our OSIRIS REx spacecraft will travel all the way to the surface of Bennu, an asteroid, during this sample collection attempt. The spacecraft will contact the surface for several seconds then collect a sample, which it will return to Earth in 2023.

launches.launchName: SpaceX Crew 1 Mission to the International Space Station
launches.launchDescription: Crew Dragon commander Michael Hopkins, pilot Victor Glover, and mission specialist Shannon Walker of NASA and Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (JAXA) mission specialist Soichi Noguchi will launch on the Crew 1 mission from Launch Complex 39A at Kennedy Space Center in Florida.
The James Webb Space Telescope will find the first galaxies that formed in the early universe and peer through dusty clouds to see stars forming planetary systems.
